You create $total_marks as a simple variable. So, it has one value - the value for everyone. It needs to be an array. Don&#39;t set it to zero - set it to an empty array.

    $total_marks = array();

As you loop through the student array, create an index in your total marks array and initialize it to zero:

    $total_marks[$student] = 0;

IMPORTANT NOTE: You are reusing $key in two for loops. Bad practice!

Now, when you add to the total marks value, add it only to that one index:

    $total_marks[$student]+= $get_marks;

When you are done, $total_marks will be an array, one element per student.

